    "recap_headline": "TCU",
    "recap_text": "FORT WORTH\n\u2013 UCF used two big innings to hand TCU an 18-7 loss on Friday night at Lupton Stadium.\nThe Rundown\nUCF raced out to an 8-0 lead in its first two offensive innings. A two-out single in the first put the Knights in front 1-0. Thirteen batters made their way to the plate in the second and seven came round to score.\nTCU got on the board in the bottom of the second.\nKyuss Gargett\nsingled with one out. A defensive miscue in left on a\nColton Griffin\nbase knock allowed Gargett to score from first. UCF got the run back in the top of the fifth to make it a 9-1 ballgame.\nThe Horned Frogs didn't go quietly as they batted around in the fifth and scored five times to pull within three. A walk and back-to-back hits from\nJack Bell\nand\nCole Cramer\nloaded the bases with nobody out. The first run scored on a\nSawyer Strosnider\nsacrifice fly. Hits from\nChase Brunson\nand\nNolan Traeger\ndrove in two more runs. Griffin grounded out to drive in another run and\nRob Liddington\nlegged out an infield single to make it a 9-6 ballgame.\nStrosnider's one-out home run in the sixth brought the Frogs within two, 9-7.\nThat was as close as the Frogs would get as UCF scored nine runs in the final two innings to put the game away.\nMason Brassfield\n(2-2) took the loss after allowing eight runs on eight hits in 1 2/3 innings. He struck out three and walked two.\nStat of the Game:\n2 \u2013\nUCF batted around in two innings, scoring a combined 15 runs in the second and ninth inning.\nNotes:\n\u2022 TCU tallied double-digit hits (12) for the seventh time this season.\n\u2022 TCU homered in a game for the 15\nth\ntime this season.\n\u2022 TCU registered a stolen base in a game for the 16\nth\ntime this season.\n\u2022 TCU issued a season-high 12 walks in the game.\n\u2022\nMason Brassfield\nregistered his 100\nth\ncareer strikeout in the game.\n\u2022\nCole Cramer\ntallied his fifth multi-hit game of the season and the 44\nth\nof his career.\n\u2022\nSawyer Strosnider\nhas reached safely in 37 straight games dating back to last season.\n\u2022 Strosnider tallied his 100\nth\ncareer hit in the contest.\n\u2022 Strosnider hit his seventh home run of the season and now has 18 in his career.\n\u2022 Strosnider posted his seventh multi-RBI game of the season and the 20\nth\nof his career.\n\u2022\nNolan Traeger\ntallied his fifth multi-hit game of the season and the 19\nth\nof his career.\n\u2022\nKyuss Gargett\ncollected his third multi-hit game of the year and the 10\nth\nof his career.\n\u2022\nColton Griffin\nhas reached safely in 12 straight games.\nNext Up:\nWith the loss, TCU falls to 12-9 on the season and 1-3 in Big 12 play.\u00a0TCU and UCF will meet Game 2 of the series Saturday night. First pitch is set for 5 p.m. The game will be televised on ESPN+.",
